        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(whatsapp): add native location send + action routing",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add native location send support to WhatsApp outbound adapter (`sendLocation`)\n- wire `message.send` latitude/longitude flow through gateway + outbound runner\n- expose WhatsApp `location` action in plugin action runtime\n- add validation and tests across WhatsApp, gateway send handler, and outbound runner\n\n## Why this fixes the previous core break\nThe previous patch-only attempt applied `wire` changes without the base `sendLocationWhatsApp` implementation, which caused build/runtime missing-export failures.\nThis PR includes both commits together **plus** a compatibility fix for current `main` (`mediaAccess` now required in `ResolvedActionContext` for location action calls).\n\n## Validation\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/whatsapp/src/send.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/send-api.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/action-runtime.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel-react-action.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/send.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.send-validation.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.core-send.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior or issue addressed: native WhatsApp location pins now honor gateway execution mode and keep canonical metadata.\n\nReal environment tested: Carlos’s Mac mini with the live OpenClaw WhatsApp setup.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/whatsapp/src/send.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/action-runtime.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel-react-action.test.ts`\n- live WhatsApp location send from the OpenClaw session using `message.send` with `latitude`, `longitude`, `locationName`, and `locationAddress`\n\nEvidence after fix: Console output\n```\nmessage.send location -> 3EB024E0649082A17CF421\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the WhatsApp client received a native location pin, not plain text.\n\nWhat was not tested: full repo-wide vitest suite; broad runs were getting SIGKILL earlier, so I used focused coverage plus a live send.\n\n## Notes\n- Error path for unsupported channels now returns `unsupported location channel: <channel>`.\n- Includes latitude/longitude range validation and optional location metadata (`locationName`, `locationAddress`, `accuracyInMeters`).\n",
